  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1140 mg
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP. Dice @tomato{2}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, half the tomatoes, half the cilantro, and a splash of @red wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine half the @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with 1/4 tsp @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Add @water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper, sliced onion, and a big pinch of salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and tender, ~{7-8%minutes}.

Stir in remaining tomatoes, remaining southwest spice blend, and 2 TBSP water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are softened and mixture is thickened and saucy, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If veggie mixture seems dry, add up to 2 TBSP more water.

Remove from heat; stir in remaining cilantro and remaining sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.

Use pan used for chicken or turkey here.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; sprinkle one half of each tortilla with @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Top with veggie filling, then sprinkle with @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup}.

Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Add chicken or turkey to tortillas along with veggie filling.

Wash out pan used for veggie filling; return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.

Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheeses have melted, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

> Depending on the size of your pan, you may need to work in batches.

Cut quesadillas into wedges; divide between plates and top with @guacamole{4%tablespoon} and salsa. Drizzle with crema and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.